    "ui_why_aaw": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"ui-feature-shell\">\n  <section class=\"ui-section dark\">\n    <div class=\"ui-wrap\">\n      <div class=\"ui-section-head\">\n        <p class=\"ui-kicker\">Why AAW</p>\n        <h2>What Makes an AAW Universal Different</h2>\n        <p>Many brands offer universal IEMs. AAW approaches them with the same driver expertise, tuning rigour, and hand-built quality control that defines our custom monitors. A universal from AAW is not a stripped-back product \u2014 it is the same acoustic instrument, in a shell built to welcome you.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ui-approach-grid\" style=\"margin-top:28px;\">\n        <div class=\"ui-approach-card\">\n          <h3>The Same Voice as Our Customs</h3>\n          <p>Models like Mockingbird, Halcyon, and A3H+ Lux are available as both universals and customs. The driver count, crossover topology, and tuning target are identical across the two. When you audition the universal, you are listening to exactly the sound the custom delivers \u2014 only the shell changes.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ui-approach-card\">\n          <h3>Tubeless by Design</h3>\n          <p>Our Z Series \u2014 Z07, Z06, Z05 \u2014 uses a tubeless sound path where drivers fire into a resonance-controlled chamber rather than traditional acoustic tubing. The result is reduced tube resonance, cleaner upper-treble, and a more open soundstage \u2014 engineered into a universal form factor.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ui-approach-card\">\n          <h3>LiquidMorph: Semi-Custom Comfort</h3>\n          <p>Included with select AAW universals, LiquidMorph tips are a proprietary silicone that softens with body heat and gently conforms to your ear canal over a few minutes of wear. They offer a near-custom seal without the lead time of a custom shell \u2014 bridging convenience and intimacy with elegance.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ui-approach-card\">\n          <h3>Two Monitors in One</h3>\n          <p>The Z05 AuAg features TwinCore \u2014 a mechanical switch that reconfigures the crossover network between two distinct voicings. Two presentations, one body. It is a rare gesture in this category, and it reflects the AAW philosophy of putting the listener in command of the sound.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ui-approach-card\">\n          <h3>FitMorph Geometry</h3>\n          <p>The Z07 wears a shell shape refined across thousands of ear scans, distributing weight evenly across the concha. The result is a universal that feels closer to a custom \u2014 secure during movement, stable for long performances, and comfortable for the long listen home.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"ui-approach-card\">\n          <h3>Tested and Heard, Every Pair</h3>\n          <p>Every AAW universal passes through our analyser for channel matching and frequency response, and through a final listening check by the same technicians who finish our flagship customs. There is no batch sampling \u2014 your pair was inspected, measured, and approved by ear.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"ui-note\" style=\"margin-top:28px;\">\n        <strong>Audition the Full Range in Singapore</strong>\n        <p>Visit our showroom at 76 Playfair Road, #01-03 LHK2 Building and hear every AAW universal side by side. Compare the Z07 against the Mockingbird, the Halcyon against the Z05 AuAg, the A3H+ Lux against the M20 \u2014 and find the tuning that fits your music. <a href=\"/pages/contact\" style=\"color:#e2b768;\">Book an appointment</a> or walk in during business hours.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>",
